 Smith open for buisness</span><hr size=1> Currently I have an over 200 skill in Smithing. I have a few conditions I feel are a necessary evil cause of the difficulty of finding stuff to make fp with. I will try and be as detailed but to the point as possible. BTW, on a price comparison my prices were found to be very fair as long as you dont mind a 1 week delivery time (no cash up front).<br>
<br>
Here is my price list :<br>
<br>
Bracer - 90pp<br>
BP - 300pp<br>
Boots - 170pp<br>
Gorget - 80pp<br>
Cloak - 240pp<br>
Gauntlets - 170pp<br>
Belt - 120pp<br>
Greaves - 250pp<br>
Helm - 170pp<br>
Pauldron - 200pp<br>
Vambraces - 130pp<br>
Visor - 90pp<br>
<br>
Total Suit price with 1 bracer I will do for - 1800pp<br>
<br>
Total Visual Suit with 1 bracer I'll do for - 1k<br>
<br>
Dye's<br>
<br>
These are the components and where they are found.<br>
<br>
Permafrost Crystals - Blue - dropped by mobs in perma<br>
Jack'o'lantern Fungus - Yellow - Unrest and Karana Jacks<br>
Sarcoscypha Fungus - Pink to Red - Unrest, Upper Guk and Fungus men in Innothule swamp<br>
Evergreen Leaves - Green - found on the ground in the morning in Gfay and Lfay (look for bags on the ground)<br>
Charcoal - Black - Fire Elementals in Lavastorm and Najeena, Mist Ele's in EC<br>
Russet Oxide - Rust(Yellow Brown) - Earth Elementals everywhere<br>
Iron Oxide - Rust (Red Brown) - Earth Elementals everywhere<br>
<br>
Also, in order to create the dye to color the armor it requires getting/buying a few items. Here is the process..<br>
<br>
<br>
Item + Empty Vial + water Flask (Combined By a Alchemist/Posioner)= Extract<br>
then...<br>
Extract + Med Jar (pottery) + resins (see below requirements for shade) = Dye<br>
then...<br>
Dye + Jar of Laquer + Jar of Acid + Armor Piece = Dyed Armor<br>
<br>
And these are your shades<br>
<br>
1 resin = dark shade<br>
2 resin = basic or med shade<br>
3 resin = light shade<br>
<br>
cost per 1 dark shade = 15pp<br>
cost per 1 med shade = 20pp<br>
cost per 1 light shade = 25pp<br>
<br>
With Dyes I will request you bring me the components for the colors you want since they aren't too common and its a pain running around finding them all the time just to sell them as cheap as I do. I can take the component from there and turn it into the dye at the prices above.<br>
<br>
Delivery time<br>
<br>
Individual pieces I will try and make to order. (DISCLAIMER - of course if you ask me to make a piece just before a dragon raid I'm afraid you're gonna have to wait till the next morning)<br>
<br>
 Plain full suits should be a 1 week delivery unless I have multiple orders and then I will get them done as quickly as possible in the order I recieved them.<br>
<br>
Dyed full suits will be 1 - 2 weeks delivery since I need to get ahold of my alchemist guildmate to make the dye itself.<br>
<br>
<br>
To order a suit pls state what pieces, size, 1 bracer or 2 and if dyed what colors. I can meet anywhere needed to do the exchange as long as its a &quot;main&quot; area (have access to a druid)<br>
<br>
